OL,3,CPope Francis cancels meeting with Rome
OL,4,Cdeacons due to illness
OL,6,FWhen asked about his health in a
OL,7,Frecent television interview, Francis
OL,8,Fquipped what has become his standard
OL,9,Fline: "Still alive, you know."
OL,11,FOver the past two years, Francis has
OL,12,Findicated several times that he would
OL,13,Fbe ready to step down, following the
OL,14,Fexample of his predecessor, Benedict
OL,15,FXVI, if his health deteriorates to the
OL,16,Fpoint that it becomes an impediment to
OL,17,Fhim leading the Catholic Church.
OL,19,FHowever, in a TV interview last month,
OL,20,Fhe said he felt in good health and
OL,21,Fdenied immediate plans to resign.
